args:
The prince visits the town of Quinbell, where a
local lady named Catherine asks for help with
their summer festival. When a social outcast
named Eugene refuses to pitch in, the two have
an altercation which is interrupted by the
appearance of a curious and lovely creature.

Comparisons are a common thing
As rocs are set against the merles
Though miles apart, we're yet alike
All are but fools, so let us whirl

Weeeell, if it isn't Eugene! Man, when you
told Catherine you weren't gonna help with
the summer festival, I thought every vein
in her forehead was gonna burst.
Oh, er... Um... Yeah, I guess.
Dunno why she even cared, honestly.\nWaste of space like that... Don't make a\ndifference whether he pitches in or not.
Festivals are stupid anyway. It's way better\nfor me to chill with you here, right, Sam?

Quinbell: A country town in South Grastaea that
enjoys cultural interchange with Hinomoto.
In honor of this relationship, the town hosts an
annual summer festival in the Hinomotoan style.
Whoa, check out the festival stage!\nWonder what the deal with this thing is?
As I understand it, people surround\nthe stage and perform what's called\na bon dance.

Dude, that sounds like fun on a bun!
I wish we had one of these thingies
back at the Halidom so ol' Notte
could cut some rug.

I wonder if a bon dance resembles a
traditional ballroom dance? Two people
joining hands and gazing lovingly into
each other's eyes... Eeeee!
The bon dance is not a partnered affair,\nbut rather a solo one.
Ribbon? In place! Skirt? Of the finest cut!\nLuxurious curls? PERFECTION!

I am pleased to make your acquaintances,
good people of the Halidom. My name is
Catherine, and I am the acting mayor of
Quinbell. Oho! Oho ho ho ho!
Please allow me to welcome you to our\ntown. You must be the representatives\nof the festival planners, yes?
That's right. Unfortunately, Yaten and the\nothers are pretty busy this time of year,\nso they asked us to come in their place.
You have my gratitude. And to show it,\npermit me to offer you these coupons\nfor use at the night shops.
That is SO perfectly you, Cat!\nEver-so-slightly magnanimous!
So long as I hold the reins, this year's\nfestival shall be a vision of perfection!
I've even summoned a special guest,\nwhich ensures all will have a rollicking\ngood time! Oho ho ho!
Miss Catherine, this is terrible! All the\nmembers of the young people's\norganization are wiped out!
Message for you, Cat! She says the young\npeople's organization has been wiped out.\n...Wait, WHAT?!
I fear they all overdid themselves with\nthe festivities last night, and they're\nin no shape to be going out.

But they were responsible for escorting
tourists, running the night shops, and
everything else besides! Oh dear, I fear
we may have to postpone the festi—
Resolutely and absolutely NOT!\nThere will be no further talk of\ncanceling my perfect festival.
Cat, you know I love you, but this festival\nrequires a ridiculous amount of manpower.\nHow are we supposed to get around that?
If our labor force is running low,\nwe'll simply have to recruit from\ndifferent quarters.
And why, may I ask, are you looking\nin our direction?
If wagging tongues are to be believed,\na great deal of your work at the Halidom\ninvolves the helping of others.
And ON that note, I would like to formally\nrequest your assistance in ensuring that\nmy summer festival is sheer perfection!
She's asking, but I don't think she's\nACTUALLY asking...
I don't mind helping. Heck, there are\nplenty of folks in the Halidom who love\nputting on big events like this.
Cat, we can't just ask these people to help\nfor FREE—that would be terribly gauche.

Indeed it would, Sandy. And in that case,
perhaps our reserve materials for the
stage might serve as payment? Then you
can build your own in the Halidom.
A hometown bon dance? Yes! BIG yes!\nAll of us! Notte speaks for everyone\nat the Halidom in this matter!

Well, I'm glad that's settled. Now then,
chop chop, everyone! We've plenty of
work to do, and little time to do it.
Oho! Oho ho ho ho ho!

This Halidom certainly does seem to be
bursting with highly talented people.
Perhaps tomorrow's festival will be
a grand success after all!
What is it, Cat? You look troubled.

The people in charge of procuring items
and managing the festival are mostly from
the Halidom—which means OUR festival
is in danger of becoming THEIR festival.
If this is anyone's festival, it is MINE.\nAt the very least, we need to get the\nassistance of more Quinbellians.

We're an older town, Cat, and this kind
of work requires a lot of heavy lifting.
We may not have any more young
people who CAN help.
Well, there is one—though I fear\nhe's rather dour and craven.
You can't possibly mean Eugene, can you?
He might be better than nothing.\n＂Might＂ being the operative word...
Still, it is intolerable to think that boy is\njust sitting on his hands and not helping\none whit with my summer festival!
Sandy! Becky! Take care of things here!\nI have a slacker to wrangle.
All right, my turn now. I rolled a ten,\nso my light infantry gets to advance.
Hardening your defenses with heavy\ncavalry? In that case, my next move is—
EUGEEEEEENE! GET OUT HERE AT ONCE!
Crap, it's the one-woman idiot brigade.\nWe gotta hide, Sam!

I know you're in there sucking down nougat
and playing those absurd board games!
If you don't come out this instant, I shall
break down your front door myself!

Hmm. Perhaps he's actually gone out.
I don't see how anyone could have heard
that speech and resisted its charms.
Well, I suppose I'll be off! La de dum...
Looks like we slipped the idiot trap.
I KNEW you were here! Next time I knock,\nyoung man, I expect you to come bounding\nforth with the speed of a thousand hares.
Oh, stop fussing over a measly door.\nGreat minds dwell not on small matters.
It's not small! It costs money and all to get\nit fixed! What do you even WANT, gosh?

The people from the youth organization
have all been felled by exhaustion, and
your help with the festival is better than
no help at all. ...Probably.
Yeah, I don't help with stupid crap.
People who go to festivals and talk about\ndumb stuff like making summer memories\nare all empty-headed morons.

They'll be like, ＂Oh, we don't want to get
separated!＂ and use it as an excuse to
hold hands and be all over each other
and barfy stuff like that.
I wouldn't help with that junk if you kicked\nin all my doors. Heck, you can kick ME!\nGo on! Kick me to death! I'll never help!
As ever, I have absolutely NO idea\nwhat you are on about.
In any case, I came here to get you myself,\nso it's time to suck it up and be grateful.\nNow get to thanking me! Haaaah!
Wh-wha?! No! Lemme go, you crazy lady!
Heavens above, what IS that creature?!
